text:
Thank you <@UG7S8J18D>, I appreciate your help. I  have cut and pasted the global_fonts and global_colors groups from fields.json from the boilerplate and referenced them in my css file to set &lt;body&gt; and &lt;p&gt; selectors in the same way as the boiler plate themes-override.css file you shared.

All of the fields show up in the page editor Design tab, but I still can't get anything on that page to actually change font or text color.

It appears that my css is not actually pulling through information from the json file. When I inspect the css file when viewing the published page in Chrome developer tools. the &lt;body&gt; and &lt;p&gt; selectors have no styling information on the font and color fields referenced by my css file.

*Here's the pertinent segment from my css file:*

{% set body_font = theme.primary_font %}

body {
   max-width: 70%;
   {{body_font.font}};

}
p {
  {{ body_font.font }};
}

*...And here's what shows up in Developer Tools:*

body {
max-width: 70%;
;

}
p {
  ;
}

Seems odd to me, but I'm sure I am just overlooking something obvious. Thoughts?
